This document summarizes all the business insights derived from the SQL analysis performed on the Zepto-style grocery dataset.
The insights help in understanding product performance, pricing patterns, inventory status, and revenue potential.

ðŸ“Œ 1. Out-of-Stock Analysis

A total of 453 products were found to be out of stock.

Categories with high out-of-stock counts may indicate:

High customer demand

Poor inventory management

Reordering delays


ðŸ“Œ 2. Duplicate Product Names

Multiple products share the same name.

Indicates:

Multiple variations of the same item (sizes, weights)

Potential duplicate entries in the dataset

Useful for SKU consolidation and inventory optimization.


ðŸ“Œ 3. Zero-Priced Products

Some products had:

mrp = 0

discountedSellingPrice = 0

These entries were removed as they represent invalid data.

Helps ensure reliable pricing insights.


ðŸ“Œ 4. Pricing Conversion

MRP and discounted prices were originally in paise, converted to rupees.

Ensures accuracy in financial calculations like revenue and discount percentages.


ðŸ“Œ 5. Top 10 Best Value Products

Products with the highest discount percentages were identified.

These can be promoted more aggressively for customer attraction.

Helps in planning discounts and promotional strategies.


ðŸ“Œ 6. High-MRP Products Out of Stock

Products with MRP > 300 and marked out of stock suggest:

High-demand premium items

Lost revenue opportunities

Need for faster restocking cycles


ðŸ“Œ 7. Estimated Revenue by Category

Revenue = discountedSellingPrice Ã— availableQuantity

